{
  "texts": [
    "On the other hand, \"intelligence\" refers to a computer's capability to learn, understand, and reason independently, similar to a human (Russell and Norvig, 2010).",
    "Nevertheless, there is currently no widely accepted consensus on precisely defining intelligence (e.g., Wang, 2019).",
    "Instead, more philosophical notions of intelligence, such as weak AI and strong AI (Searle, 1980), are often employed to distinguish between varying levels of machine intelligence (Russell and Norvig, 2010).",
    "While machine learning (ML) is often used interchangeably with AI, they are not identical.",
    "Machine learning is a subset of AI and denotes a set of techniques for solving data-related problems without explicit programming (Kühl et al., 2020)."
  ]
}